trans-unit.source: The DeleteChildAccessRule class represents a specific type of access rule that is used to allow or deny an Active Directory Domain Services object the right to delete child objects.
trans-unit.target: Klassen DeleteChildAccessRule representerer en bestemt type tilgangsregel som brukes til å gi eller avslå en Active Directory Domain Services-objektet rettighet til å slette underordnede objekter.

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.DeleteChildAccessRule"></xref> class with the specified identity reference and access control type.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.DeleteChildAccessRule"> </xref> klassen med angitt ID referanse og tilgang kontrolltypen.

trans-unit.source: If you use this constructor, it creates a delete child access rule that applies to all child types.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du bruker denne konstruktøren, opprettes det en tilgangsregel for Slett underordnede som gjelder for alle underordnede typer.

trans-unit.source: An <xref href="System.Security.Principal.IdentityReference"></xref> object that identifies the trustee of the access rule.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Security.Principal.IdentityReference"> </xref> -objekt som identifiserer trustee for tilgangsregelen.

trans-unit.source: One of the <xref href="System.Security.AccessControl.AccessControlType"></xref> enumeration values that specifies the access rule type.
trans-unit.target: Én av de <xref href="System.Security.AccessControl.AccessControlType"> </xref> nummereringsverdier som angir regeltypen tilgang.
